  "commentary": "With SPX at 7099.82 sitting right between the negative gamma pocket at 7115 (-4159.9M) and positive gamma wall at 7100 (+5042.1M), dealers are likely providing modest support here as they hedge long gamma positions by buying the dip. The PIN regime with 49.3B in total GEX creates a strong mean-reverting environment, with the massive 7200 strike (+7488.9M) acting as a significant selling wall that should cap upside momentum. Key levels to watch are the 7100 support wall below and 7115 negative gamma zone above - a break above 7115 could trigger dealer buying that accelerates moves toward the 7150-7200 resistance zone.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to chop between 7100 support and 7150 resistance with limited upside past 7200.",
